==English==
===Etymology===
[[lip]] + shortened form of [[synchronize]]
===Verb===
'''lip-sync'''

#To move lips in [[synchronization]] with sounds (generally recorded) so it appears they are the source of the sounds.
#:''She '''lip-synced''' to her own recording during the show because of her [[laryngitis]].''
#:''There was a grreat scandal when it was discovered the singer had been only '''lip-syncing'''.